                    CLOUD SERVICES
                    ─────────────────────────────
                    ├── Supabase (ONE project, multi-tenant via RLS)
                    ├── Claude API (shared, per-request billing)
                    ├── Stripe (billing)
                    ├── Telegram Bot API (one bot, routes by chat_id)
                    └── Vercel (engine-site + engine-app)
```

No per-client VPS. No per-client Supabase project. No per-client n8n instance.

### 10.2 Why this is better

| Aspect | Per-client VPS (v4.1) | Multi-tenant (v5) |
|--------|----------------------|-------------------|
| New client setup | 3-4 hours | 0 (CORE) / 15 min (GUIDED) |
| Infra to maintain | N servers | 1 server |
| Feature update | Deploy to N instances | Deploy once |
| Cross-client learning | Impossible | Built-in |
| Cost per client | €26-71/mo infra | ~€5-10/mo (API costs only) |
| Client capacity | Max 15 | Hundreds |
| Time to first value | 4 days | 5 minutes |

### 10.3 Agent architecture

Same principle as v4.1. Claude agent with tool-use. n8n for webhooks and crons.

```
Telegram message (any client)
    → n8n webhook
    → Extract chat_id → lookup tenant_id
    → Load tenant config (goals, schedule, system prompt overrides)
    → Claude API with tools + tenant context
    → Tool calls: manage_goal, log_progress, etc. (all scoped to tenant_id)
    → Claude generates response
    → n8n sends response back to that client's chat
```

**Multi-tenant routing is just one lookup.** The chat_id maps to a tenant. Every subsequent Supabase query includes `WHERE tenant_id = X`. That's it.

