## 15. RISKS & MITIGATIONS

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| No signups at €97/mo | 14-day free trial. Lower to €67/mo if needed. The bar is low. |
| Clients don't engage | System escalates after 3 days silence. Pattern: non-responders churn by week 3 — address proactively. |
| Claude API costs spike | Use Sonnet (cheap). Batch non-critical operations. Fall back to Ollama for IE. |
| Multi-tenant data concern | RLS + clear privacy policy. Data export on request. Three DEDICATED tiers for clients who need more. |
| DEDICATED hardware management | Mac Mini's are assets — repurpose on churn. Don't buy hardware speculatively. First client pays for first Mini. |
| Supabase free tier limits | Upgrade to Pro (€25/mo) when >50k rows. That's ~50 active clients — a good problem. |
| Too many CORE clients, no time | CORE is fully automated. Only GUIDED costs time. Cap GUIDED at 10. |
| Telegram bot rate limits | 30 msg/sec is plenty. 100 clients × 3 messages/day = 300/day. No issue. |
| Feature bloat | CORE tier is frozen after Phase 1. New features go to GUIDED/FULL STACK only. |

